From 59a93c1b017c7ac598ddbe27db0ea0511f3028e3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Pacheco <git@michaelpacheco.org>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 02:49:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] fix(popup): guard m_resource->m_surface in
 coordsRelativeToParent

CPopup::coordsRelativeToParent() dereferences the weak pointer
m_resource->m_surface after only checking m_resource for validity. During
client teardown a popup can outlive its XDG surface resource (it lingers
while fading out, with visible() still returning true for m_fadingOut),
so m_resource->m_surface is expired here. Reading
m_current.geometry.pos() off the dangling resource segfaults in
CBox::pos().

This path is reached when a layer surface unmaps (CLayerSurface::onUnmap
-> simulateMouseMovement -> mouseMoveUnified -> getSurfaceBoxGlobal ->
CPopup::coordsGlobal) and a fading-out popup is hit-tested mid-destroy.

Guard m_resource->m_surface as well, matching every other access site in
this file (onUnmap, onCommit, the popupsAt walk). Affects v0.55.4 and
current main (function unchanged after the geometricBox refactor).
---
 src/desktop/view/Popup.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/desktop/view/Popup.cpp b/src/desktop/view/Popup.cpp
index 0b87f384..19def536 100644
--- a/src/desktop/view/Popup.cpp
+++ b/src/desktop/view/Popup.cpp
@@ -381,7 +381,7 @@ PHLLS CPopup::layerOwner() const {
 Vector2D CPopup::coordsRelativeToParent() const {
     Vector2D offset;
 
-    if (!m_resource)
+    if (!m_resource || !m_resource->m_surface)
         return m_lastPos;
 
     WP<CPopup> current = m_self;
-- 
